16:610:16:12:90:10:Times New Roman:Ke ywor ds: satellite   navigation,   GLONA SS,   d ifferentia l   correction,   intersatellite measure ment, 
16:611:12:12:90:10:Times New Roman:autonomous navigation 
16:612:12:13:62:4:Times New Roman: 
16:613:13:18:90:12:Times New Roman:When  modeling the operating processes of ballistics and navigation support it  is expedient 
16:614:18:17:62:12:Times New Roman:to make decomposition  of  the  general  problem  of  coordinate-time  and  navigation  support into 
16:615:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:the typical options of its engineering implementation. 
16:616:17:17:90:12:Times New Roman:As the satellite navigation technologies the paper considers inter-satellite measurement and 
16:617:17:18:62:12:Times New Roman:autonomous  navigation  mode of  differential  correction.  It  also  assesses the  possibility  of  their 
16:618:18:17:62:12:Times New Roman:application to improve the accuracy of navigation determinations. 
16:619:17:17:90:12:Times New Roman:Technologies using inter-satellite measurement tools such as GLONASS / GPS equipment, 
16:620:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:equipment of inter-satellite radio link, astro-optical space based devices are an independent class 
16:621:17:18:62:12:Times New Roman:of navigation technologies. 
16:622:18:17:90:12:Times New Roman:However, each of these options has both advantages and disadvantages that affect the eval-
16:623:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:uation of the appropriateness and feasibility of their use. 
16:624:17:17:90:12:Times New Roman:The  paper  separately considers  the  problem  of  increasing survivability  of  space  systems 
16:625:17:18:62:12:Times New Roman:and  conservation  of  ground  control  complex due  to  introduction  of  requirements  to  ensure  the 
16:626:18:17:62:12:Times New Roman:independent functioning of spacecraft and application of technologies of ballistics and navigation 
16:627:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:support, supposing  to  involve minimum  means of automated  ground  control  complex for  these 
16:628:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:purposes. 
16:629:17:18:90:12:Times New Roman:Currently, there  is a completely developed theory of autonomous  navigation based on  as-
16:630:18:17:62:12:Times New Roman:tronomical positional gauges, which are used as onboard optical sensors of orientation and stabi-
16:631:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:lization systems. 
16:632:17:18:90:12:Times New Roman:To date, the differential navigation mode is, virtually, the only approach that can allow the 
16:633:18:17:62:12:Times New Roman:solution of tasks in terms of increased accuracy, but with some restrictions. 
16:634:17:17:90:12:Times New Roman:The implementation of differential mode of treatment is carried out through the creation of 
16:635:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:differential subsystems of the satellite navigation systems.  These subsystems are usually divided 
16:636:17:18:62:12:Times New Roman:into wide-range, regional and local ones. 
16:637:18:17:90:12:Times New Roman:Analysis of ballistic aspects to  implement discussed navigation technologies allowed  us to 
16:638:17:17:62:12:Times New Roman:identify constraints for  improving accuracy to  define consumers  of  the satellite  navigation  in-
16:639:17:0:62:12:Times New Roman:formation. 
